Sentencas: Results are presented on a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material designed for use with C-containing fuels: a composite of an electronically conducting ceramic, La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-delta, an ionically conducting ceramic, Ce(0.9)Gd(0.1)O(1.9)5 (GDC), and a small fraction Ni.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These ceramic-based anodes were tested in SOFCs with GDC bulk electrolytes.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode performance was comparable to that for Ni-GDC anodes with hydrogen and methane fuels.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anodes also provided good performance with propane and butane and, unlike Ni-GDC, there was little or no coking.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 4 wt % Ni content in the anode was necessary to obtain good performance, indicating that a small amount of Ni provides a substantial electrocatalytic effect while not causing coking.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Initial cell test results showed good cell stability and indicated that the anodes were not affected by cyclic oxidation and reduction.
Titulo: A fuel-flexible ceramic-based anode for solid oxide fuel cells
